{
  "texts": [
    "Interestingly, the multimodal research changed paradigms in 2021 and was predominantly directed towards basic applications, namely grading and subtyping.",
    "An increase in publications was observed in 2022, including both basic and advanced studies, culminating in a total of seven publications.",
    "An expansion was observed in 2023 as well, not only focusing on prognosis predictions but also introducing mutation predictions for the first time in the field.",
    "This trend hints at the growing recognition and potential of multimodality in histopathology and genomics, a progress that will probably increase in importance in the forthcoming years.",
    "DiscussionA first difference between DL in histopathology and genomics emerges when comparing the sheer number of publications."
  ]
}